Stage 1 — Azure Knowledge Store Implementation Plan
Goal

Build the Phase 0 knowledge storage layer in Azure so the system can store:

stable Optisweep context
normalized incidents
timeline events
workflow definitions
reusable procedures
raw evidence
source artifacts
escalation summaries
relationships between all of the above

The storage layer should support retrieval now and workflow/procedure refinement later.

Recommended Azure Storage Architecture
Use 3 storage services
Service	Purpose	Why
Azure Cosmos DB for NoSQL	Primary structured database	Flexible JSON documents, good for evolving schemas, relationships, metadata, versioning
Azure AI Search	Retrieval/search index	Best for RAG, hybrid keyword + vector retrieval, citations, filters
Azure Blob Storage	Raw files and artifacts	Best for screenshots, source docs, logs, PDFs, exported case files

Azure AI Search supports hybrid full-text and vector retrieval, which is what you want for RAG-style troubleshooting search. Blob Storage is the right place for unstructured source files and artifacts like documents, screenshots, logs, and exports. Cosmos DB is a practical source-of-truth store because it can store flexible JSON documents and also supports vector/hybrid search if you later want to simplify architecture or experiment with Cosmos-based retrieval.

Important Design Rule

Do not use Azure AI Search as the database.

Use:

Cosmos DB = source of truth
Azure AI Search = searchable retrieval index
Blob Storage = raw source artifact storage

This keeps the system clean.

Recommended Azure Resource Names

Use simple, phase-specific names.

Resource Group:
rg-optisweep-ai-phase0

Cosmos DB Account:
cosmos-optisweep-phase0

Cosmos DB Database:
optisweep_knowledge_phase0

Azure AI Search:
srch-optisweep-phase0

Storage Account:
stoptisweepphase0

Blob Containers:
raw-source-artifacts
processed-source-artifacts
Cosmos DB Database Design
Database Name
optisweep_knowledge_phase0
Containers

Create one Cosmos DB container per major dataset.

Container	Dataset	Purpose
context_reference	Dataset 0	Stable domain/context knowledge
incident_records	Dataset 1	Canonical incident records
timeline_events	Dataset 1.5	Incident timeline events
workflow_definitions	Dataset 2A	Versioned workflow definitions
procedure_dictionary	Dataset 2B	Reusable procedures
raw_evidence_chunks	Dataset 3	Source evidence chunks
source_artifacts	Dataset 4	Metadata for raw files, screenshots, logs
escalation_summaries	Dataset 5	Engineer handoff summaries
knowledge_relationships	Cross-dataset	Links incidents, workflows, procedures, symptoms, causes, evidence
ingestion_runs	Operational metadata	Tracks manual ingestion jobs
Partition Key Recommendation

For Phase 0, keep this simple.

Container	Partition Key
context_reference	/context_type
incident_records	/issue_category
timeline_events	/incident_id
workflow_definitions	/issue_category
procedure_dictionary	/procedure_type
raw_evidence_chunks	/incident_id
source_artifacts	/incident_id
escalation_summaries	/incident_id
knowledge_relationships	/from_id
ingestion_runs	/run_type

This is good enough for Phase 0 and keeps querying straightforward.

Container 1 — context_reference
Purpose

Stores stable Optisweep domain knowledge that should not be mixed with incident retrieval.

Examples:

