Recommended workflow creation rule

Use this logic:

Situation	Action
New incident matches existing workflow strongly	Link incident to workflow
New incident mostly matches but has a variation	Create workflow refinement candidate
New incident has repeated pattern across multiple cases	Propose new workflow
New incident is isolated or uncertain	Store as incident evidence only
SME approves candidate	Promote to approved workflow
Existing workflow becomes outdated	Create new version or deprecate
Add a workflow_candidates container

I would add one more container:

workflow_candidates

Purpose:

Stores proposed workflows or proposed changes to existing workflows generated from incident ingestion. These are not runtime workflows until SME approved.

Example:

{
  "id": "wfc_heartbeat_timeout_refinement_229716",
  "candidate_type": "refinement",
  "source_incident_ids": ["229716"],
  "target_workflow_id": "heartbeat_timeout_no_rms_alarm_v1",
  "proposed_change": "Add escalation condition for remote access unavailable or VPN/ZScaler outage.",
  "reason": "Incident 229716 resolution was delayed because remote access was unavailable.",
  "evidence_refs": ["inc_229716"],
  "status": "needs_sme_review",
  "created_at": "2026-05-15T00:00:00Z"
}
Updated storage distinction
Storage Area	Meaning
incident_records	What happened
timeline_events	What happened in sequence
procedure_dictionary	Reusable operational actions
workflow_definitions	Approved or draft decision trees
workflow_candidates	Proposed new workflows or refinements
knowledge_relationships	Links between incidents, procedures, workflows, symptoms, evidence
The principle to give Cursor
Historical incidents should teach the system. They should not become the system one-for-one.